Confluence Search & Fetch Agent Architecture

Objective

Build an intelligent agent-driven system to fetch, rank, and extract relevant information from Confluence and search sources to generate accurate, context-aware responses.

Enable seamless integration with existing agentic RAG systems and UI-triggered workflows.


---

Overview

This system introduces an agent orchestrator that dynamically decides which tools to invoke (Confluence fetch, search APIs, etc.) and processes results through ranking and extraction pipelines.

It supports:

Intelligent tool selection (agent-driven or predefined flow)

Multi-source retrieval (search + Confluence)

Relevance-based ranking and summarization

Response generation using top results



---

High-Level Architecture

User Query
   ↓
Intent Extractor (CQL Generator)
   ↓
Agent Orchestrator
   ├── Confluence Search Tool (MCP)
   ├── External Search Tool (MCP)
   ↓
Fetch Top N URLs (e.g., 30)
   ↓
Ranking Engine (Relevance Scoring)
   ↓
Top 3 URL Selection
   ↓
Content Extraction
   ↓
Response Generator (LLM)
   ↓
Final Answer


---

Core Functionalities

1. Query Processing

Accept user query

Extract intent

Convert into Confluence Query Language (CQL) or search query


2. Agent Orchestration

Decide:

Which tool(s) to call (Confluence / Search / Both)

Whether to follow dynamic reasoning or predefined pipeline



3. Search & Retrieval

Fetch up to 30 URLs/documents

Sources:

Confluence pages

External/internal search APIs



4. Ranking Engine

Rank results based on:

Query relevance

Content similarity

Metadata signals


Select Top 3 most relevant URLs


5. Content Extraction

Extract useful sections from selected pages

Handle:

Structured Confluence pages

Linked URLs within pages



6. Linked URL Handling

Detect embedded/linked Confluence URLs

If relevant, include them in extraction pipeline


7. Response Generation

Use extracted content

Generate concise, accurate response using LLM



